criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult (> 18 years old);

          -  Clinical and laboratory diagnosis of Prediabetes or Diabetes Mellitus (type 1 or type
             2);

          -  Clinical compensation (glycemic control);

          -  No cognitive limitation (score ≥ 4 in the six-item screener);

          -  No confirmed diagnosis of cardiovascular diseases such as unstable coronary artery
             disease (CAD), heart failure; use of a pacemaker and/or implantable
             cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD), intermittent claudication; no recent cardiovascular
             event or cardiac surgery (≤ 6 months);

          -  Participants not currently enrolled in a structured physical exercise program that
             follows diabetes guidelines.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Clinical decompensation that contraindicates the performance of physical exercises
             (not glycemic control);

          -  Physical and/or mental limitations that will prevent the participant to perform
             physical exercises and/or understanding of educational content;

          -  Complex ventricular arrhythmias (i.e., atrial flutter or atrial fibrillation, multiple
             atrial or ventricular ectopy, and atrioventricular or ventricular block.
